cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.DC 

This paper deals with optimization of resource allocation and load balancing in heterogeneous cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques and information theory, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses coordination between different cells and the joint optimization of multiple parameters, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
